AUDIENCE: You're done, right?

00:42:02.810 --> 00:42:03.000
AJAHN BRAHM: Yeah.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:03.430
Done it.

00:42:03.430 --> 00:42:03.660
Yeah.

00:42:03.660 --> 00:42:04.159
But look.

00:42:04.159 --> 00:42:07.140
This is the case in many
religions in our world.

00:42:07.140 --> 00:42:09.300
There is no equity.

00:42:09.300 --> 00:42:10.510
You see the priests.

00:42:10.510 --> 00:42:11.630
You see the imams.

00:42:11.630 --> 00:42:14.680
You see the gurus,
and they're all male.

00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:17.060
Does that mean that
females are suddenly

00:42:17.060 --> 00:42:19.125
spiritually inadequate?

00:42:19.125 --> 00:42:21.680
That you can't have them as
our teachers and leaders?

00:42:21.680 --> 00:42:24.450
We have the Dalai Lama,
a male, the pope, a male,

00:42:24.450 --> 00:42:26.390
the ayatollah's male.

00:42:26.390 --> 00:42:28.560
They're all male.

00:42:28.560 --> 00:42:31.620
Where are the females?

00:42:31.620 --> 00:42:33.120
And one other thing
about Buddhism.

00:42:33.120 --> 00:42:35.120
In the earliest time,
when the Buddha was alive,

00:42:35.120 --> 00:42:36.120
there was equity.

00:42:36.120 --> 00:42:37.240
We did have bhikkunis.

00:42:37.240 --> 00:42:39.350
They're the female monks.

00:42:39.350 --> 00:42:40.690
And we have the male monks.

00:42:40.690 --> 00:42:43.800
We had equality there
from 2,500 years ago.

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:45.514
We lost it somehow.

00:42:45.514 --> 00:42:47.180
And so now we sort
of start it up again.

00:42:47.180 --> 00:42:49.620
So to start it up
again, you have

00:42:49.620 --> 00:42:53.360
to go against the hierarchy,
against the bosses.

00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:56.080
If anyone has the
opportunity to hire,

00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:59.950
you just hire, no
matter what they say.

00:42:59.950 --> 00:43:02.560
That's what I had to do,
to stand up and say, look.

00:43:02.560 --> 00:43:04.720
I don't care what my bosses say.

00:43:04.720 --> 00:43:05.720
This needs to be done.

00:43:05.720 --> 00:43:06.550
I'm going to do it.

00:43:06.550 --> 00:43:10.340
So you just go ahead and do
it for the state of equity.

00:43:10.340 --> 00:43:14.010
There are always ways of
having affirmative action.

00:43:14.010 --> 00:43:17.000
But for goodness' sake,
stop all the bullshit

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:18.810
of talking about it.

00:43:18.810 --> 00:43:19.790
You have to do it.

00:43:19.790 --> 00:43:22.830
Too many talking about it,
too many conferences, too

00:43:22.830 --> 00:43:25.780
many papers written about
the necessity of this.

00:43:25.780 --> 00:43:27.720
But somehow you've got to do it.

00:43:27.720 --> 00:43:29.790
And one of the stories
which inspired me.

00:43:29.790 --> 00:43:32.840
In my home country
of Australia, there

00:43:32.840 --> 00:43:35.810
was an equity for the gay
community, gay, lesbian,

00:43:35.810 --> 00:43:37.380
transgenders.

00:43:37.380 --> 00:43:41.620
And one of the last
outposts of stupidity

00:43:41.620 --> 00:43:46.330
was the state of Tasmania,
where until very recently,

00:43:46.330 --> 00:43:51.290
it was illegal, against the
law, with a custodial penalty,

00:43:51.290 --> 00:43:55.470
for gay people to
have consensual sex.

00:43:55.470 --> 00:43:59.290
And the gay community
in Tasmania, for years,

00:43:59.290 --> 00:44:03.350
they were trying to get the
government to overturn this.

00:44:03.350 --> 00:44:05.350
And the government
said, don't worry.

00:44:05.350 --> 00:44:07.160
We'll not prosecute anybody.

00:44:07.160 --> 00:44:09.750
But that was just
so patronizing,

00:44:09.750 --> 00:44:13.156
to say there's no
problem when there is.

00:44:13.156 --> 00:44:16.042
The men can't see the problem.

00:44:16.042 --> 00:44:17.690
The females can.

00:44:17.690 --> 00:44:18.680
It is a problem.

00:44:18.680 --> 00:44:21.850
So don't be patronizing and
think there's not a problem.

00:44:21.850 --> 00:44:24.460
So what these people did--
they were really smart.

00:44:24.460 --> 00:44:29.420
Those 50 gay couples
decided one night

00:44:29.420 --> 00:44:32.530
they would have as
much sex as possible.

00:44:32.530 --> 00:44:37.440
And they wrote it all down in
detail, what they had done.

00:44:37.440 --> 00:44:39.670
And afterwards, the
following morning,

00:44:39.670 --> 00:44:42.730
they handed themselves
in to the cops.

00:44:42.730 --> 00:44:44.180
They said, we confess.

00:44:44.180 --> 00:44:45.210
We committed a crime.

00:44:45.210 --> 00:44:46.300
We did this sex.

00:44:46.300 --> 00:44:47.610
And we signed it.

00:44:47.610 --> 00:44:49.850
This is what we did.

00:44:49.850 --> 00:44:54.050
And 50 couples, with all the
media in tow-- and the police

00:44:54.050 --> 00:44:56.390
had no choice.

00:44:56.390 --> 00:44:58.770
They had to arrest these people.

00:44:58.770 --> 00:45:02.200
And these were good people
who committed a crime.

00:45:02.200 --> 00:45:07.040
And they confessed-- we did
it-- and were put in jail.

00:45:07.040 --> 00:45:09.960
And of course, only two
or three days later,

00:45:09.960 --> 00:45:12.400
the state parliament
overturned that law

00:45:12.400 --> 00:45:16.050
because they were
so embarrassed.

00:45:16.050 --> 00:45:21.370
So embarrassment is a
way to get things done.

00:45:21.370 --> 00:45:24.130
That's why I was
excommunicated, because I

00:45:24.130 --> 00:45:29.410
embarrassed my bosses so badly,
they wanted to get rid of me.

00:45:29.410 --> 00:45:31.025
So please, embarrass
your bosses.

00:45:34.230 --> 00:45:37.890
One way of doing that, just
what comes to my head-- OK.

00:45:37.890 --> 00:45:41.290
Those people who support
gender equity in Google--

00:45:41.290 --> 00:45:45.631
