00:46:43.850 --> 00:46:45.242
in the office.

00:46:45.242 --> 00:46:48.170
And it's making a statement.

00:46:48.170 --> 00:46:50.950
Because sometimes there's too
much talk, not enough action.

00:46:50.950 --> 00:46:52.300
That doesn't get you anywhere.

00:46:52.300 --> 00:46:54.206
So that's my suggestion for you.

00:46:54.206 --> 00:46:56.080
Next Monday, or you can
make it another week,

00:46:56.080 --> 00:46:57.380
come dressed as a woman.

00:46:57.380 --> 00:46:59.390
Get as many people on board.

00:46:59.390 --> 00:47:00.020
100, 200.

00:47:00.020 --> 00:47:01.570
You won't be so embarrassed.

00:47:01.570 --> 00:47:02.660
And you make a statement.

00:47:02.660 --> 00:47:04.118
There's not enough
women in Google.

00:47:04.118 --> 00:47:06.501
So we're going to
pretend to be women.

00:47:06.501 --> 00:47:07.000
OK.

00:47:07.000 --> 00:47:09.890
Does that make any-- yeah.

00:47:09.890 --> 00:47:10.769
Go on.

00:47:10.769 --> 00:47:12.560
AUDIENCE: When did you
decide to be a monk,

00:47:12.560 --> 00:47:14.679
and why did you
decide to be a monk?

00:47:14.679 --> 00:47:16.970
AJAHN BRAHM: It's because I
used to be a school teacher

00:47:16.970 --> 00:47:19.470
in high school for one year.

00:47:19.470 --> 00:47:22.340
And that would make anyone
think of leaving the world.

00:47:22.340 --> 00:47:23.780
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:25.220 --> 00:47:28.215
Have you ever had-- teaching
high school kids all day?

00:47:28.215 --> 00:47:29.120
So, anyway, no.

00:47:29.120 --> 00:47:32.330
The main reason was I always
wanted a job in my life

00:47:32.330 --> 00:47:33.930
which would give
happiness to others

00:47:33.930 --> 00:47:36.626
and which would give
happiness to myself.

00:47:36.626 --> 00:47:38.000
And by being a
spiritual teacher,

00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:39.730
you get huge
amounts of happiness

00:47:39.730 --> 00:47:43.080
through meditation,
leading a very simple life.

00:47:43.080 --> 00:47:45.970
You never have to worry about
money and possessions and stuff

00:47:45.970 --> 00:47:47.280
like that.

00:47:47.280 --> 00:47:49.070
And you have such
an easy, free life.

00:47:49.070 --> 00:47:50.820
So you get so much
happiness for yourself.

00:47:50.820 --> 00:47:53.170
And now in my life,
I have opportunities

00:47:53.170 --> 00:47:56.990
to go and teach others and
really help them big-time.

00:47:56.990 --> 00:47:59.670
And amazing, the
power you can get as a

00:47:59.670 --> 00:48:02.970
monk actually to help
people in the social level.

00:48:02.970 --> 00:48:06.100
The last couple of talks
I gave, sometime ago,

00:48:06.100 --> 00:48:07.160
always on YouTube.

00:48:07.160 --> 00:48:09.900
Many of you have
seen me on YouTube.

00:48:09.900 --> 00:48:14.430
We have questions coming
about the talk from Syria.

00:48:14.430 --> 00:48:19.170
So these teachings, these
talks can go all over the world

00:48:19.170 --> 00:48:21.810
and go to a place like
Syria, which is probably

00:48:21.810 --> 00:48:24.650
the country with the most
suffering at this moment,

00:48:24.650 --> 00:48:25.910
the most problems and trouble.

00:48:25.910 --> 00:48:28.070
And you give one
talk, it's streamed,

00:48:28.070 --> 00:48:29.690
and people actually
know about it.

00:48:29.690 --> 00:48:30.530
They can log in.

00:48:30.530 --> 00:48:31.840
And they can listen
to the talk, and they

00:48:31.840 --> 00:48:34.173
can ask questions in all these
other parts of the world.

00:48:34.173 --> 00:48:35.860
That gives me a
lot of happiness.

00:48:35.860 --> 00:48:39.580
And you can find
ways-- psychologists,

00:48:39.580 --> 00:48:43.650
they come and learn their
stuff from monks like me.

00:48:43.650 --> 00:48:45.850
This mindfulness stuff,
that came from Buddhism.

00:48:45.850 --> 00:48:48.360
There's so much
psychology, which

00:48:48.360 --> 00:48:50.350
I've seen psychologists using.

00:48:50.350 --> 00:48:51.750
And I know where they came from.

00:48:51.750 --> 00:48:54.620
Me.

00:48:54.620 --> 00:48:56.820
Because you see these
things, you spread it around,

00:48:56.820 --> 00:48:59.970
and it really helps big-time.

00:48:59.970 --> 00:49:01.680
Little things like
my story of opening

00:49:01.680 --> 00:49:04.990
the door of your heart,
where my father taught me

00:49:04.990 --> 00:49:07.540
what the meaning of
unconditional love was.

00:49:07.540 --> 00:49:09.540
He took me aside when
I was only about 13.

00:49:09.540 --> 00:49:12.080
And he said to me,
son, wherever you

00:49:12.080 --> 00:49:15.320
go in your life, whatever
you do, however you turn out,

00:49:15.320 --> 00:49:18.030
the door of my house will
always be open to you.

00:49:18.030 --> 00:49:18.970
That's what he said.

00:49:18.970 --> 00:49:21.640
But his house was so
small and so poor,

00:49:21.640 --> 00:49:23.730
he'd never locked the door.

00:49:23.730 --> 00:49:24.969
He wasn't afraid of burglars.

00:49:24.969 --> 00:49:27.260
In fact, he was hoping a
burglar would come in one day,

00:49:27.260 --> 00:49:31.280
take pity on us, and
leave us something.

00:49:31.280 --> 00:49:33.450
But that's actually pretty true.

00:49:33.450 --> 00:49:38.065
But I realized later on in my
life, he didn't mean his house.

00:49:38.065 --> 00:49:40.700
He meant his heart.

00:49:40.700 --> 00:49:43.800
He man, you're my son.

00:49:43.800 --> 00:49:46.600
Whatever you turn out
like, wherever you go,

00:49:46.600 --> 00:49:51.200
whatever you do, you're my
son, and the door of my heart

00:49:51.200 --> 00:49:54.080
I will never close against you.

00:49:54.080 --> 00:49:56.460
The door of my heart's
always open to you.

00:49:56.460 --> 00:49:58.640
That meant so much to me.

00:49:58.640 --> 00:50:02.180
And I've taught that to
so many other people.

00:50:02.180 --> 00:50:04.970
And the next step is to
say to yourself, no matter

00:50:04.970 --> 00:50:09.790
who you are, one day in some
quiet moment of your life,

00:50:09.790 --> 00:50:12.860
whoever I am,
whatever I have done,

00:50:12.860 --> 00:50:19.010
even the abuse I've given out
or received in my life so far,

00:50:19.010 --> 00:50:22.660
the door of my heart is
open to all of that as well.

00:50:22.660 --> 00:50:24.760
Come in.

00:50:24.760 --> 00:50:26.520
It's an incredible,
powerful moment,

00:50:26.520 --> 00:50:28.970
because in the
extreme cases I've

00:50:28.970 --> 00:50:33.600
been teaching in an organization
called Assets in Australia,

00:50:33.600 --> 00:50:37.330
Australian Society of Survivors
of Torture and Trauma,

00:50:37.330 --> 00:50:39.450
people who have been in
these really dark places

00:50:39.450 --> 00:50:43.790
in the world-- tortured,
multiple rape-- survive

00:50:43.790 --> 00:50:47.700
and come to places like
Australia's refugees--

00:50:47.700 --> 00:50:49.610
physically, they're free.

00:50:49.610 --> 00:50:52.560
Emotionally, they're still in
those dark dungeons underground

00:50:52.560 --> 00:50:54.500
being tortured.

00:50:54.500 --> 00:50:59.400
How on earth can you give
them the emotional freedom?

00:50:59.400 --> 00:51:01.200
And the people
there say, the story

00:51:01.200 --> 00:51:05.500
which works the best is
what I've just taught you.

00:51:05.500 --> 00:51:08.940
There comes a time
when these survivors

00:51:08.940 --> 00:51:13.970
imagine their little heart
and two doors opening.

00:51:13.970 --> 00:51:15.860
Just like in the
old aircraft, little

00:51:15.860 --> 00:51:18.930
steps coming down to the ground.

00:51:18.930 --> 00:51:22.030
And on the ground
outside of their heart

00:51:22.030 --> 00:51:27.310
is those little girls who
were raped, who were tortured.

00:51:27.310 --> 00:51:32.830
Parts of themselves, it's very
hard to embrace and bring in.

00:51:32.830 --> 00:51:36.460
Kept outside for years.

00:51:36.460 --> 00:51:40.320
And inviting those little
beings up the staircase

00:51:40.320 --> 00:51:46.060
into your heart, not to only get
rid of them but embracing them.

00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:47.756
They're part of you.

00:51:47.756 --> 00:51:49.756
And these people imagine
that, these people that

00:51:49.756 --> 00:51:53.480
have been tortured,
beaten, half killed,

00:51:53.480 --> 00:51:56.190
walking timidly up the steps.

00:51:56.190 --> 00:51:58.725
And the other part of you, the
part of you which you like,

00:51:58.725 --> 00:52:02.980
which you're proud of,
embracing these people,

00:52:02.980 --> 00:52:07.360
bringing them in,
and being one again.

00:52:07.360 --> 00:52:09.470
That is powerful.

00:52:09.470 --> 00:52:11.310
That comes from me.

00:52:11.310 --> 00:52:13.300
And that works.

00:52:13.300 --> 00:52:14.840
So when I can do
stuff like that,

00:52:14.840 --> 00:52:16.770
that gives me
enormous happiness.

00:52:16.770 --> 00:52:19.390
That is why I'm a monk.

00:52:19.390 --> 00:52:21.140
AUDIENCE: Thank you,
Ajahn, for your talk.

00:52:21.140 --> 00:52:24.100
I heard you speaking very
clearly about kindness.

00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:25.810
And last night
with Eugene Cash, I

00:52:25.810 --> 00:52:28.510
asked the question of
caring for or transforming

00:52:28.510 --> 00:52:30.750
habitual reactions.

00:52:30.750 --> 00:52:33.990
And he expressed regret that I
had missed your talk on Sunday

00:52:33.990 --> 00:52:34.780
there last week.

00:52:34.780 --> 00:52:35.570
AJAHN BRAHM: Yeah.

00:52:35.570 --> 00:52:39.070
AUDIENCE: And I hoped if there
was some seed more of that you

00:52:39.070 --> 00:52:40.560
care to share with us.

00:52:40.560 --> 00:52:41.470
AJAHN BRAHM: OK.

00:52:41.470 --> 00:52:45.860
When you care for
something, it gets less.

00:52:45.860 --> 00:52:49.150
There's a classic story
in Buddhism, which I also

00:52:49.150 --> 00:52:54.020
use in psychology, which is
the story of the monster who

00:52:54.020 --> 00:52:56.840
came into the emperor's palace.

00:52:56.840 --> 00:53:02.060
So a long time ago, there
was a monster, a demon.

00:53:02.060 --> 00:53:04.640
It was so ugly and
so frightening.

00:53:04.640 --> 00:53:07.020
And he came into
an emperor's palace

00:53:07.020 --> 00:53:10.830
when she was away
on some business.

00:53:10.830 --> 00:53:15.890
And this monster was so ugly and
frightening that all the guards

00:53:15.890 --> 00:53:18.580
and soldiers and security
which was supposed

00:53:18.580 --> 00:53:20.950
to guard the place, they hid.

00:53:20.950 --> 00:53:23.210
They went under the
tables, through the doors.

00:53:23.210 --> 00:53:26.880
They hid because they were
terrified of this monster.

00:53:26.880 --> 00:53:31.000
And that allowed the monster to
go right into the central hall

00:53:31.000 --> 00:53:34.350
and sit on the empress's throne.

00:53:34.350 --> 00:53:36.830
And that was going too far.

00:53:36.830 --> 00:53:39.740
So the soldiers, the
ministers, even the cooks,

00:53:39.740 --> 00:53:42.440
everybody who worked in
the palace, they said,

00:53:42.440 --> 00:53:43.500
get out of here.

00:53:43.500 --> 00:53:44.370
You don't belong.

00:53:44.370 --> 00:53:46.840
Who do you think you are?

00:53:46.840 --> 00:53:50.920
And at those few unkind
words, unkind deeds,

00:53:50.920 --> 00:53:56.020
and unkind thoughts, the monster
grew an inch bigger, more ugly,

00:53:56.020 --> 00:53:58.250
more smelly, more offensive.

00:53:58.250 --> 00:54:00.260
That made them mad.

00:54:00.260 --> 00:54:01.480
They threatened.

00:54:01.480 --> 00:54:02.490
They cursed.

00:54:02.490 --> 00:54:05.700
But every unkind word,
deed, or thought,

00:54:05.700 --> 00:54:09.290
the monster just grew an inch
bigger, more ugly, more smelly,

00:54:09.290 --> 00:54:10.690
more offensive.

00:54:10.690 --> 00:54:15.390
By the time the empress came
back, this monster was huge.

00:54:15.390 --> 00:54:21.070
It was so frightening, it makes
Alien look like pussycats.

00:54:21.070 --> 00:54:26.780
And was so smelly that
even the maggots crawling

00:54:26.780 --> 00:54:29.090
on the monster's
skin, they barfed.

00:54:29.090 --> 00:54:30.120
They threw up.

00:54:30.120 --> 00:54:34.730
Not even maggots could
stand the stench.

00:54:34.730 --> 00:54:40.722
And the empress, she was in
that job because she was smart.

00:54:40.722 --> 00:54:42.370
Not like Google.

00:54:42.370 --> 00:54:44.960
They get empresses on
the basis of ability,

00:54:44.960 --> 00:54:46.580
not the basis of gender.

00:54:46.580 --> 00:54:51.920
[LAUGHS]

00:54:51.920 --> 00:54:56.120
And she knew what to do.

00:54:56.120 --> 00:54:59.450
She said, welcome, monster.

00:54:59.450 --> 00:55:02.780
Thank you so much
for dropping in.

00:55:02.780 --> 00:55:06.820
Has anyone got you
a cup of tea yet?

00:55:06.820 --> 00:55:08.470
We've got green tea.

00:55:08.470 --> 00:55:09.760
We've got black tea.

00:55:09.760 --> 00:55:10.970
We've got peppermint tea.

00:55:10.970 --> 00:55:12.865
It's good for your health.

00:55:12.865 --> 00:55:16.540
And was really sincere
with her kindness.

00:55:16.540 --> 00:55:20.320
And they noticed every kind
word or thought or deed,

00:55:20.320 --> 00:55:23.080
the monster grew an
inch smaller, less ugly,

00:55:23.080 --> 00:55:24.805
less smelly, less offensive.

00:55:24.805 --> 00:55:27.660
So everyone realized
their mistake.

00:55:27.660 --> 00:55:30.670
They were now kind
to the monster.

00:55:30.670 --> 00:55:34.250
Someone rang out for a
pizza, because now it

00:55:34.250 --> 00:55:37.220
comes monster-size.

00:55:37.220 --> 00:55:39.940
Another five people
gave him a foot massage.

00:55:39.940 --> 00:55:42.850
Have you ever had reflexology?

00:55:42.850 --> 00:55:45.955
Really rare for a monster to
get his big feet massaged.

00:55:45.955 --> 00:55:47.547
And he was just
really enjoying it.

00:55:47.547 --> 00:55:48.630
He goes, over there a bit.

00:55:48.630 --> 00:55:49.130
Oh, yeah.

00:55:49.130 --> 00:55:50.620
Ooh, that's nice.

00:55:50.620 --> 00:55:53.067
At every kind word,
kind act, kind thought,

00:55:53.067 --> 00:55:55.400
the monster just shrank a
little bit smaller, less ugly,

00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:58.466
less smelly, less offensive,
until the monster soon

00:55:58.466 --> 00:56:00.590
got to the size that he
first came into the palace.

00:56:00.590 --> 00:56:02.700
But they never stopped
with their kindness.

00:56:02.700 --> 00:56:04.410
They carried on being
kind to the monster

00:56:04.410 --> 00:56:07.960
until one more act of
kindness, and the monster

00:56:07.960 --> 00:56:10.760
shrank completely away.

00:56:10.760 --> 00:56:16.810
And the Buddha said we call
those anger-eating monsters.

00:56:16.810 --> 00:56:19.330
You give them anger, and
they get bigger, more

00:56:19.330 --> 00:56:22.530
of a problem, more trouble.

00:56:22.530 --> 00:56:26.150
How many anger-eating
monsters can you see?

00:56:26.150 --> 00:56:27.454
Even an addiction.

00:56:27.454 --> 00:56:28.620
I don't want this addiction.

00:56:28.620 --> 00:56:30.551
Get out of here.

00:56:30.551 --> 00:56:33.700
It can get worse.

00:56:33.700 --> 00:56:36.730
So that's what I
mean by kindness.

00:56:36.730 --> 00:56:42.140
Kindness makes many problems
get smaller, more tractable,

00:56:42.140 --> 00:56:45.000
more possible to fix.

00:56:45.000 --> 00:56:47.000
But when you get angry
at them, get out of here.

00:56:47.000 --> 00:56:48.380
You don't belong.

00:56:48.380 --> 00:56:51.390
One of the greatest, most
common anger-eating monsters

00:56:51.390 --> 00:56:54.830
which we have is cancer.

00:56:54.830 --> 00:56:56.790
Tumor, get out of here.

00:56:56.790 --> 00:56:59.350
You don't belong.

00:56:59.350 --> 00:57:03.510
I've been going to the cancer
support groups in Australia

00:57:03.510 --> 00:57:05.866
for over 25 years now.

00:57:05.866 --> 00:57:07.360
And I keep going back there.

00:57:07.360 --> 00:57:10.690
They keep inviting me,
because what I say works.

00:57:10.690 --> 00:57:13.420
Any of you who follow
that stupid tradition

00:57:13.420 --> 00:57:17.844
of fighting your cancer--
some people manage to win.

00:57:17.844 --> 00:57:19.260
But a lot of people
lose who could

00:57:19.260 --> 00:57:26.090
have won if they were kind,
relaxed, instead of fighting.

00:57:26.090 --> 00:57:28.070
Fighting, you get more tense.

00:57:28.070 --> 00:57:31.210
The very reason those cancers
began in the first place,

00:57:31.210 --> 00:57:34.700
you're encouraging
them to continue.

00:57:34.700 --> 00:57:36.110
This is powerful stuff.

00:57:36.110 --> 00:57:38.120
Because I don't if
you've had any people

00:57:38.120 --> 00:57:41.740
you really love die of cancer
or anyone who's got cancer now

00:57:41.740 --> 00:57:44.260
or will get cancer.

00:57:44.260 --> 00:57:46.730
It's a stress-related disease.

00:57:46.730 --> 00:57:48.730
You give it more
stress-- get out here.

00:57:48.730 --> 00:57:53.320
I don't want you-- it
gets worse, bigger.

00:57:53.320 --> 00:57:54.040
Yeah?

00:57:54.040 --> 00:57:55.940
AUDIENCE: So you
talked a lot about sort

00:57:55.940 --> 00:58:00.940
of managing anger, managing
problems, and accomplishing

00:58:00.940 --> 00:58:02.710
things by putting things down.

00:58:02.710 --> 00:58:05.460
Can you speak a little bit
about the subject of doubt?

00:58:05.460 --> 00:58:08.137
Because as we
proceed through life

00:58:08.137 --> 00:58:09.720
and as we try to
accomplish the things

00:58:09.720 --> 00:58:12.220
that we set out for ourselves,
the goals we've set,

00:58:12.220 --> 00:58:13.820
there's always this
underlying doubt

00:58:13.820 --> 00:58:18.740
about whether the direction
we're taking ourselves in

00:58:18.740 --> 00:58:20.080
is the correct one.

00:58:20.080 --> 00:58:24.380
And in an uncertain world,
this is almost impossible

00:58:24.380 --> 00:58:28.760
to sort of, I
guess, make go away.

00:58:28.760 --> 00:58:31.020
So how do you address
this question?

00:58:31.020 --> 00:58:31.850
AJAHN BRAHM: OK.

00:58:31.850 --> 00:58:33.680
Doubt, the Buddha
used to say, is

00:58:33.680 --> 00:58:35.105
like being lost in the desert.

00:58:35.105 --> 00:58:36.736
There's this guy
lost in the desert

00:58:36.736 --> 00:58:37.860
for days and days and days.

00:58:37.860 --> 00:58:40.870
He was crawling on
his hands and knees.

00:58:40.870 --> 00:58:43.540
Heat stroke, sun stroke,
everything stroke.

00:58:43.540 --> 00:58:45.340
Maybe a few minutes,
and he would die.

00:58:45.340 --> 00:58:47.940
And in the distance, he
saw a mirage, he thought.

00:58:47.940 --> 00:58:49.792
Because he saw someone
coming towards him.

00:58:49.792 --> 00:58:51.250
But he hadn't seen
anyone for days.

00:58:51.250 --> 00:58:52.166
The middle of nowhere.

00:58:52.166 --> 00:58:54.150
He thought, this can't be true.

00:58:54.150 --> 00:58:58.340
And as he looked,
it looked as if it

00:58:58.340 --> 00:59:02.770
was an Eskimo, an
Inuit with a dog sled

00:59:02.770 --> 00:59:05.125
and eight husky dogs in front.

00:59:05.125 --> 00:59:08.680
And he thought, the
sun is making me crazy.

00:59:08.680 --> 00:59:10.400
It must be a mirage.

00:59:10.400 --> 00:59:13.250
But as it came closer, he
could make out the sound

00:59:13.250 --> 00:59:14.750
of the husky dogs barking.

00:59:14.750 --> 00:59:18.250
And he could see the
furs of the Eskimo.

00:59:18.250 --> 00:59:20.150
And he thought, my goodness.

00:59:20.150 --> 00:59:21.270
I'm actually saved.

00:59:21.270 --> 00:59:23.540
It's not a mirage after all.

00:59:23.540 --> 00:59:28.020
And soon, he could feel the
huskies licking his face,

00:59:28.020 --> 00:59:30.190
and he could see
the Eskimo there,

00:59:30.190 --> 00:59:32.000
standing right before him.

00:59:32.000 --> 00:59:33.040
It's a miracle.

00:59:33.040 --> 00:59:34.670
I'm saved, he said.

00:59:34.670 --> 00:59:37.480
I've been lost in the desert
for days, he said to the Eskimo.

00:59:37.480 --> 00:59:40.350
And the Eskimo said, and
you think you're lost.

00:59:45.170 --> 00:59:53.860
But going back-- going
back to the story,

00:59:53.860 --> 00:59:55.110
it's being lost in the desert.

00:59:55.110 --> 00:59:57.230
And there happened to be
a case when I was young.

00:59:57.230 --> 01:00:00.560
I was lost in the mist in
the mountains of Scotland,

01:00:00.560 --> 01:00:02.190
way up in the mountains.

01:00:02.190 --> 01:00:04.860
I was lost, didn't
know which way to go.

01:00:04.860 --> 01:00:08.320
And I was told stories of these
people who'd been going around

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:11.750
and round in the mist for
days, and they never came out.

01:00:11.750 --> 01:00:13.830
Some people died.

01:00:13.830 --> 01:00:14.920
This was really dangerous.

01:00:14.920 --> 01:00:16.253
You didn't know which way to go.

01:00:16.253 --> 01:00:18.700
You had no sense of
direction at all.

01:00:18.700 --> 01:00:21.399
So I was really
scared because I could

01:00:21.399 --> 01:00:23.440
have been up there for a
long time without water,

01:00:23.440 --> 01:00:25.310
without food.

01:00:25.310 --> 01:00:30.980
But then I got back to my
basic science, gravity.

01:00:30.980 --> 01:00:33.480
Water always goes downhill.

01:00:33.480 --> 01:00:35.580
So I found a little
stream, a tiny stream,

01:00:35.580 --> 01:00:37.669
and decided to follow that,
whichever way it went.

01:00:37.669 --> 01:00:39.710
And I followed it and
followed it and followed it

01:00:39.710 --> 01:00:40.376
and followed it.

01:00:40.376 --> 01:00:42.240
It always went further
and further down.

01:00:42.240 --> 01:00:44.230
Because I knew if you
went down far enough,

01:00:44.230 --> 01:00:46.964
you go below the
clouds, below the mist,

01:00:46.964 --> 01:00:48.380
and you can actually
see your way.

01:00:48.380 --> 01:00:49.580
And that's what I did.

01:00:49.580 --> 01:00:52.160
Soon I was below the mist.

01:00:52.160 --> 01:00:54.420
And I could say the way home.

01:00:54.420 --> 01:00:57.186
And that's a simile
I use for doubt.

01:00:57.186 --> 01:00:59.680
Yeah, you can't see
the big picture.

01:00:59.680 --> 01:01:02.102
You're not below the mist yet.

01:01:02.102 --> 01:01:06.040
But at least you know
that water goes downhill.

01:01:06.040 --> 01:01:08.860
You know that whatever you're
doing, saying, however you're

01:01:08.860 --> 01:01:13.420
living, if it is creating
better good, happiness,

01:01:13.420 --> 01:01:15.710
peace, whatever qualities
you want to grow,

01:01:15.710 --> 01:01:18.230
if those qualities
are increasing,

01:01:18.230 --> 01:01:19.780
you're going in the
right direction.

01:01:19.780 --> 01:01:21.640
Carry on.

01:01:21.640 --> 01:01:23.710
You can't see the big
picture, the big goal,

01:01:23.710 --> 01:01:26.650
but you know that what
you're doing in your life

01:01:26.650 --> 01:01:29.135
is creating a little bit
more peace, a little bit

01:01:29.135 --> 01:01:31.960
more happiness, a little bit
more harmony, whatever it is.

01:01:31.960 --> 01:01:33.880
You know you're going
in the right direction.

01:01:33.880 --> 01:01:36.340
That is the only way
you can overcome doubt

01:01:36.340 --> 01:01:38.960
until the time comes
you're below the mist

01:01:38.960 --> 01:01:42.120
and you can see exactly
which way you need to go.

01:01:42.120 --> 01:01:44.592
MING: Thank you.

01:01:44.592 --> 01:01:45.550
AJAHN BRAHM: Very good.

01:01:45.550 --> 01:01:48.000
